data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_WPNAV_SPEED_UP_Description

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_RTL_SPEED_Description

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_LOIT_SPEED_Description
data.value: Defines the maximum speed in cm/s which the aircraft will travel horizontally while in loiter mode. Increment - 0.5. Range 0.2-35. [{0:F2} cm/s] [{1:F2} km/h] [{2:F2} mi/h].

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_LAND_SPEED_Description
data.value: The descent speed for the final stage of landing in cm/s. Increment - 0.1. Range 0.3-2. [{0:F2} cm/s] [{1:F2} km/h] [{2:F2} mi/h].

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_LAND_SPEED_HIGH_Description
data.value: The descent speed for the first stage of landing in cm/s. If this is zero then WPNAV_SPEED_DN is used. Increment - 0.1. Range 0-5. [{0:F2} cm/s] [{1:F2} km/h] [{2:F2} mi/h].

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_LAND_ALT_LOW_Description
data.value: Altitude during Landing at which vehicle slows to LAND_SPEED. Increment - 0.1. Range 1-100. [{0:F2} cm] [{1:F2} ft]. Note: This parameter is for advanced users.

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_PILOT_SPEED_UP_Description
data.value: The maximum vertical ascending velocity the pilot may request in cm/s. Increment - 0.1. Range 0.5-5. [{0:F2} cm/s] [{1:F2} km/h] [{2:F2} mi/h].

data.name: SpeedsQuickParamView_PILOT_SPEED_DN_Description
